events.name: OSEA Membership Registration
events.description:
If you need any assistance in choosing your membership category, please do not hesitate to contact us at 416-977-4441.Your annual membership fee is an investment that enables OSEA to research and champion consistent and supportive political and regulatory environment necessary for Community Power proponents and the entire sustainable energy sector to thrive. For over 10 years, OSEA has been advocating progressive and inclusive energy policies that are based on international best practices. Successes to date include:
The creation of the feed-in tariff programs
The campaign for the Green Energy and Green Economy Act
The creation of the Community, Aboriginal and Municipal Energy Partnership programs
The aboriginal loan guarantee program
Creation of the Community Power Fund
The Renewable Energy Standard Offer Program
OSEA continues to consult with its members on issues of importance and research best practices to inform its regulatory work and advice to the government on how best to support the Community Power and larger sustainable energy sector.In addition to researching and advocating for best practices at the policy and regulatory level, OSEA also offers its members training, advisory and facilitation services. OSEA also holds an annual Community Power conference and other networking opportunities providing suppliers, manufacturers service providers and developer’s opportunities to collaborate and build their businesses.Membership is open to any individual or organization that wishes to support OSEA’s values, vision and mission upon approval of the membership committee.All current members are eligible to receive a discount of 15% if they renew 30 days prior to their renewal date. Membership renewal fees are due 12 months following application approval and initial fee payment. All membership applications are subject to approval of the membership committee.For any issues with payment or to renew your membership, please contact  the OSEA Office Manager, at admin(at)ontario-sea.org or by phone at 416-977-4441 ext: 1.

events.name: TXRD Lonestar Rollergirls 2016 Regular Season Pass
Flora, fashion & fine arts - cultural discovery
events.description:
Bowen Island is blessed with an abundance of natural beauty and a vibrant cultural scene. This tour is the perfect blend and exploration of both worlds. Join us for a little cultural discovery - island style.Bowen is recognized as the fifth most artistic community in Canada, with many visual artists, writers, musicians, performers and crafters call this little isle home. Add to this a unique selection of specialty stores and this tour is a pleasurable excursion with many opportunities to gift shop or pick up something for yourself.This tour includes a lovely forest walk, an introduction to Snug Cove, and a brief visit to the museum and archives. For your pleasure the tour includes one organic chocolate sample from renowned chocolatier Cocoa West. You will be introduced to the shops and galleries at Artisan Square and given time to shop on your own. If you wish to enjoy lunch or a snack, Artisan Eats offers a fine brunch/lunch menu and an array of baked goods. At the end of the tour you will be given the choice to return to Snug Cove with your guide or provided with information on how to return on your own, either by walking or by bus.Our partners include:
Artigiani Milanesi Cashmere Tailors
Artisan Eats
Arts Pacific Co-operative Gallery
Bell 'Occhio Home Decor
Bowen Island Flower Shop
Cloudflower Clayworks
Cocoa West Chocolatier
Gilt Studio Gallery
Movement Global Clothing
The Gallery@Artisan Square
Wren Boutique
*Please note: we have a bus version of this tour on select days. Please refer to our Bus Tour Arts & Shops for dates and times.Things you should know about this tour:
Please wear comfortable walking shoes, as you will be walking on mixed and uneven surfaces.
The walking distance is approximately 1 km and includes a steep hill - 2 km if you return on foot. We will walk slowly up the hill but this may still be too challenging for some people. If this is too much for you, please consider taking the bus version of this tour.
Tours run rain or shine, so please wear appropriate clothing.
This tour starts at the Visitor Information Centre, 432 Cardena, but ends at Artisan Square, where you may spend time on your own.
Tours require a minimum number of participants. Your ticket will be refunded or transferred to another date if the minimum number of participants for a specific tour is not met. We will give you 48-hour notice of any tour cancellations.
We understand that sometimes plans change. We will endeavor to accommodate changes to your tour booking, but refunds or tour rescheduling requires a minimum of 3 days notice. Please contact Jody at Bowen Island Tours directly via, email, phone or text, to discuss any cancellations or rescheduling.
We are unable to provide refunds or reschedule tours if you arrive late. Sometimes the ferry runs late and there are vehicle overloads during peak times, particularly during the summer months. So please ensure that you allow enough time for these circumstances. We do endeavour to accommodate late arrivals, but cannot guarantee that you will be able to join a tour in progress.
All tour participants are required to read and accept Bowen Island Tours' Waiver and Release of Liability before purchasing tickets. You will be asked to accept the terms at the ticket checkout. Please read the terms on Bowen Island Tours' website located on the home page, bottom footer: www.bowenislandtours.com
Please contact Jody at Bowen Island Tours if you have questions about this or any other tours.
* If you do not see a day and time that fits with your schedule, please contact us. Often our schedule changes and we can accommodate requests, advise of upcoming dates, or provide private or group tours.

events.name: Best of Bowen - explore, experience, enjoy
events.description:
Surrounded by awe-inspiring nature, majestic mountain vistas, and blue waterways, known for its friendly hospitality, relaxed lifestyle and small-town charm, Bowen Island is one of Vancouver's best day-trip and getaway destinations. Conveniently located less than one hour from the heart of the city, once you're here you'll feel like you are a world away.Join us for an authentic West Coast island adventure. Our Best of Bowen tour visits the island's most popular destinations - Snug Cove, picturesque Killarney Lake and Artisan Square. Along the way you'll experience the island's lush temperate rainforest as we meander through the trees on groomed trails. You'll learn a bit about Bowen's fun past as a seaside resort. And you'll be introduced to the island's many features, amenities and visitors' services. We hope you'll join us for a truly memorable excursion on beautiful Bowen, Vancouver's island neighbour.Things you should know about this tour:
Walking distance approximately 5.5 km. The difficulty of this walk is moderate: mostly groomed trails and a couple of short steep hills that we'll take slowly. 
Please wear comfortable walking shoes, such as runners, as you will be walking on mixed and uneven surfaces, trails with roots, rocks, and potentially other tripping hazards.
Tours run rain or shine, so please wear appropriate clothing. It is really quite lovely to walk in the forest when it is raining, as long as you are dressed for it.
This tour does not include food or drinks. Please bring water and snacks. You can purchase food in Snug Cove before the tour or at Artisan Square, our final destination. 
This tour starts at the Visitor Information Centre in Snug Cove (432 Cardena) and ends at Artisan Square, or you can walk back to the starting point with your guide.
Given the distance, this trek is not appropriate for young children. Fit and keen youth 12 and older are welcome.
Tours require a minimum number of participants. Your ticket will be refunded or transferred to another date if the minimum number of participants for a specific tour is not met. We will give you 48-hour notice of any tour cancellations.
We understand that sometimes plans change. We will endeavor to accommodate changes to your tour booking, but refunds or tour rescheduling requires a minimum of 3 days notice. Please contact Jody at Bowen Island Tours directly via, email, phone or text, to discuss any cancellations or rescheduling.
We are unable to provide refunds or reschedule tours if you arrive late. Sometimes the ferry runs late and there are vehicle overloads. Whenever possible, we do endeavour to accommodate late arrivals but cannot guarantee that you will be able to join a tour if it has started.
All tour participants are required to read and accept Bowen Island Tours' Waiver and Release of Liability before purchasing tickets. You will be asked to accept the terms at the ticket checkout. Please read the terms on Bowen Island Tours' website located on the home page, bottom footer: www.bowenislandtours.com
Please contact Jody at Bowen Island Tours if you have questions about this or any other tours.
* If you do not see a day and time that fits with your schedule, please contact us. Often our schedule changes and we can accommodate requests, advise of upcoming dates, or provide private or group tours.

events.name: Forest Trek to Xenia Island Retreat
events.description:
Immerse yourself in a "forest bath" and allow nature to soothe and revitalize. This forest walk to Xenia Island Retreat provides an opportunity to unwind, unplug and to just be. On our journey to one of the oldest homesteads on the island, we will be surrounded by Bowen’s lush temperate rainforest, woodsy fragrances, fresh air and the quiet sounds of nature. Xenia, meaning hospitality in Greek, is a rustic peaceful sanctuary, a welcoming retreat where visitors are invited to connect with the environment, with oneself and with others. We will spend approximately one hour exploring and appreciating some of Xenia’s treasures, including Opa, a 1,000-year-old giant Douglas Fir tree, an eleven-circuit stone labyrinth, and a meditation sanctuary for those who wish quiet reflection. We will rest, have time for a packed lunch, and simply enjoy the natural ambience of Xenia.  On our return to Snug Cove, we will complete our circumference of Killarney Lake, one of Bowen’s most popular destinations.Like all of Bowen Island Tours nature walks, this journey to Xenia is informed by the principles of Shinrin-yoku, a Japanese practice and term that loosely translates to forest bathing. Since the 1980s, many studies have documented the physiological and psychological benefits associated with Shinrin-yoku, such as reductions in stress, anxiety, depression, sleeplessness, cardio-vascular disease and others.If you are interested in this tour but don’t see a date listed that suits your schedule, please contact us as other dates may be available. We also welcome private and group requests.For further information about Xenia Centre, including programs, retreats and venue rentals for weddings and special events, please visit their website: xeniacentre.comThings you should know about this tour:
Walking distance approximately 12 km return trip. The difficulty of this walk is moderate: mostly groomed trails and a few short, steep hills. 
Please wear comfortable walking shoes, such as runners, as you will be walking on mixed and uneven surfaces, trails with roots, rocks, and potentially other tripping hazards.
Tours run rain or shine, so please wear appropriate clothing. It is really quite lovely to walk in the forest when it is raining, as long as you are dressed for it.
This tour does not include food or drinks. Please bring water and a packed lunch. 
This tour starts and ends at the Visitor Information Centre in Snug Cove (432 Cardena).
Given the distance, this trek is not appropriate for young children. Fit and keen youth 12 and older are welcome.

events.info: Nora Sarmiento Prüter Gerente de investigaciones de MINCODE GROUP, profesora de pregrado y postgrado de diferentes Universidades en Colombia como la Universidad del Bosque, Konrad Lorenz, UDCA, Uniagustiniana, con más de 12 años de trayectoria en docencia y e investigación en el mundo de la Psicología del Consumidor, psicoantropología de mercados, neurociencias de comportamiento y Neuromarketing. Los contenidos de sus conferencias provienen de investigaciones reales que ha realizado personalmente con su equipo de trabajo para el desarrollo del conocimiento neurocientífico relacionados con el consumidor (Consumer Neuroscience) y más de 50 estudios para el crecimiento de marcas a nivel mundial.
